article.headline: Sacred Heart 82, Monmouth, N.J. 75
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. (AP) -- Brice Brooks scored 17 points and grabbed nine rebounds as Sacred Heart overcame a 13-point deficit in the second half to beat Monmouth 82-75 on Friday night. Chauncey Hardy also had 17 points for the Pioneers (15-13, 11-6 in Northeast Conference), while Ryan Litke added 12 points and Drew Shubik had 11. Jhamar Youngblood had a game-high 31 points and eight rebounds for the Hawks (12-17, 7-10), while Marques Alston added 15 points and Dejan Delic scored 10. Monmouth was in command for most of the game, hitting 56 percent of their shots in the first half and holding a 39-28 lead at the break. They then took their biggest lead of the game when Youngblood hit a jumper with 8:10 to play, giving Monmouth a 63-50 lead. The Hawks, though, then went cold while the Pioneers came roaring back, ending the game with a 32-12 run. Sacred Heart went ahead for good when Shubik hit a 3-pointer with 3:53 left to give his team a 66-65 lead, its first of the game. They eventually sealed the win by making 10-of-12 free throws line over the final 1:09.
